{
  "texts": [
    "The findings in Table 2 highlight the effects of utilizing SF as a supplementary cementitious material on the fresh, mechanical, and durability properties of concrete.",
    "FAAhad et al. [55] observed that using a 30% FA replacement reduces workability by 15% and extends the setting time by 10%, mainly due to a decrease in the heat produced during the hydration process.",
    "Similarly, Shah et al. [56] reported that when the replacement level is increased to 40%, the setting time extends further by 25% because of slower hydration.",
    "In contrast, Paliwal and Maru [57] found that lower replacement levels, ranging from 5 to 20%, can improve workability by up to 10% and decrease the amount of bleeding by 5%.",
    "On the other hand, Huang et al. [58] noted that at very high replacement levels, from 20 to 80%, there is a considerable drop in workability, particularly at 40% replacement, where workability is reduced by 10%, and up to 25% at an 80% replacement level."
  ]
}